Key Match Events: South Africa won by 1 wicket with 16 balls remaining.
Maharaj hit a short delivery from Nawaz behind fine leg to secure the win for South Africa.
Haris Rauf's sensational diving return catch left South Africa nine down.
Shaheen Afridi's over was negotiated effectively by South Africa, despite the peril.
Shaheen Afridi drew a bottom edge off Coetzee, leaving South Africa needing 21 runs with the tail.
Aiden Markram was dismissed by Usama Mir, falling 9 runs short of a hundred.
Marco Jansen's cameo ended with a slower ball from Rauf.
David Miller was dismissed by Shaheen Afridi, feathering through to Rizwan.
Shadab Khan and Saud Shakeel added 84 for the sixth wicket.
Shadab Khan was dismissed by Coetzee in a budding partnership.
Pakistan folded with 20 balls to go, scoring 270 in 46.4 overs.
Tabraiz Shamsi and Marco Jansen took seven of the 10 wickets for South Africa.
Pre-Game Insights: Pakistan won the toss and chose to bat first.
Pakistan made two changes: Hasan Ali was ruled out due to fever, and Mohammad Nawaz returned.
South Africa made three changes: Bavuma, Shamsi, and Ngidi came in, with Hendricks, Coetzee, and Rabada missing out.
Rabada missed out due to back spasms.
Post-Match Reflections: Heartache for Pakistan, elation for South Africa as they secured a close World Cup finish.
Pakistan's inability to convert starts into big scores was highlighted as a significant issue.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Chepauk crowd, officially 29,870 strong, offered strong support for Pakistan.
Shadab Khan went off with a freak concussion after hitting his head on the ground.
South Africa's bowlers and fielders had to front up in the intense, oppressive heat.
